{
  "doc_id": "FC-LS",
  "source_pdf": "/Users/zwy/毕设/V7/data/raw/FC-LS.pdf",
  "page": 154,
  "spans": [
    {
      "span_id": "p154_s0001",
      "text": "INCITS xxx-200x Link Services Rev 1.61 November 3, 2006",
      "bbox": [
        301.08,
        37.27,
        539.95,
        47.32
      ],
      "block_index": 1,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p154_s0002",
      "text": " 135",
      "bbox": [
        518.28,
        723.59,
        537.71,
        734.7
      ],
      "block_index": 2,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p154_s0003",
      "text": "6.2.2.3  Responses to Explicit Fabric Login",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        57.65,
        298.68,
        68.76
      ],
      "block_index": 3,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p154_s0004",
      "text": "The following are possible responses the Nx_Port may receive when transmitting a FLOGI:",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        82.97,
        497.52,
        94.08
      ],
      "block_index": 4,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p154_s0005",
      "text": "a) LS_ACC reply Sequence with OX_ID equal to the OX_ID of the FLOGI, and the Common Ser-",
      "bbox": [
        106.02,
        106.97,
        540.04,
        118.08
      ],
      "block_index": 5,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p154_s0006",
      "text": "vice N_Port/F_Port bit set to one (Fx_Port) - This is the normal response to a Fabric Login re-",
      "bbox": [
        122.4,
        118.97,
        540.05,
        130.08
      ],
      "block_index": 5,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p154_s0007",
      "text": "quest.  The D_ID of the LS_ACC shall be the N_Port_ID assigned by the Fabric.  If the S_ID in",
      "bbox": [
        122.4,
        130.97,
        539.94,
        142.08
      ],
      "block_index": 5,
      "line_index": 3,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p154_s0008",
      "text": "the FLOGI was 000000h, the D_ID shall be XXXXXX.  If the S_ID in the FLOGI was 0000h ||",
      "bbox": [
        122.4,
        142.96,
        539.99,
        154.08
      ],
      "block_index": 5,
      "line_index": 4,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p154_s0009",
      "text": "YY, the D_ID shall be XXXXYY.  If the S_ID in the FLOGI was XXXXXX, the D_ID shall be",
      "bbox": [
        122.4,
        154.96,
        539.96,
        166.08
      ],
      "block_index": 5,
      "line_index": 5,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p154_s0010",
      "text": "same value of XXXXXX.  The Payload shall include the Service Parameters for the entire Fab-",
      "bbox": [
        122.4,
        166.96,
        540.0,
        178.08
      ],
      "block_index": 5,
      "line_index": 6,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p154_s0011",
      "text": "ric, a 64-bit F_Port_Name and 64-bit Fabric_Name.  The Service Parameters are as specified",
      "bbox": [
        122.4,
        178.96,
        539.97,
        190.08
      ],
      "block_index": 5,
      "line_index": 7,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p154_s0012",
      "text": "for F_Port Login in 6.6.  The applicability of the Service Parameters to Fabric Login are given in",
      "bbox": [
        122.4,
        190.96,
        539.91,
        202.08
      ],
      "block_index": 5,
      "line_index": 8,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p154_s0013",
      "text": "tables 150 and 155.  The Nx_Port may continue operation with other Nx_Ports if the",
      "bbox": [
        122.4,
        202.96,
        537.02,
        214.08
      ],
      "block_index": 5,
      "line_index": 9,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p154_s0014",
      "text": "N_Port_ID, F_Port_Name, and Fabric_Name are the same as in a previous Fabric Login or",
      "bbox": [
        122.4,
        214.96,
        540.02,
        226.08
      ],
      "block_index": 5,
      "line_index": 10,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p154_s0015",
      "text": "proceed to N_Port Login.",
      "bbox": [
        122.4,
        226.96,
        233.45,
        238.08
      ],
      "block_index": 5,
      "line_index": 11,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p154_s0016",
      "text": "b) LS_ACC reply Sequence with OX_ID equal to the OX_ID of the FLOGI, and the Common Ser-",
      "bbox": [
        106.02,
        250.96,
        540.04,
        262.08
      ],
      "block_index": 6,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p154_s0017",
      "text": "vice Nx_Port/F_Port bit set to zero (Nx_Port) This indicates a point-to-point connection with an-",
      "bbox": [
        122.4,
        262.96,
        540.01,
        274.08
      ],
      "block_index": 6,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p154_s0018",
      "text": "other Nx_Port.  The D_ID of the LS_ACC shall be the S_ID of the FLOGI.  The Payload shall",
      "bbox": [
        122.4,
        274.96,
        539.96,
        286.08
      ],
      "block_index": 6,
      "line_index": 3,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p154_s0019",
      "text": "include the Service Parameters from the FLOGI with all classes marked invalid, a 64-bit",
      "bbox": [
        122.4,
        286.96,
        539.97,
        298.08
      ],
      "block_index": 6,
      "line_index": 4,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p154_s0020",
      "text": "N_Port_Name and 64-bit Node_Name of the connected Nx_Port.  If the received",
      "bbox": [
        122.4,
        298.96,
        539.96,
        310.08
      ],
      "block_index": 6,
      "line_index": 5,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p154_s0021",
      "text": "N_Port_Name is less than its N_Port_Name, the Nx_Port proceeds to N_Port Login.  If the re-",
      "bbox": [
        122.4,
        310.96,
        539.98,
        322.08
      ],
      "block_index": 6,
      "line_index": 6,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p154_s0022",
      "text": "ceived N_Port_Name is greater than its N_Port_Name, the Nx_Port waits for PLOGI from the",
      "bbox": [
        122.4,
        322.96,
        539.94,
        334.08
      ],
      "block_index": 6,
      "line_index": 7,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p154_s0023",
      "text": "attached N_Port.",
      "bbox": [
        122.4,
        334.96,
        197.4,
        346.08
      ],
      "block_index": 6,
      "line_index": 8,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p154_s0024",
      "text": "c)",
      "bbox": [
        106.02,
        358.96,
        114.34,
        370.08
      ],
      "block_index": 7,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p154_s0025",
      "text": "F_BSY with OX_ID equal to the OX_ID of the FLOGI.  The D_ID shall be the S_ID of the FLO-",
      "bbox": [
        122.37,
        358.96,
        539.98,
        370.08
      ],
      "block_index": 7,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p154_s0026",
      "text": "GI.  The Fabric is busy.  The Nx_Port may retry the FLOGI again later. ",
      "bbox": [
        122.4,
        370.96,
        436.16,
        382.08
      ],
      "block_index": 7,
      "line_index": 3,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p154_s0027",
      "text": "d) P_BSY Sequence with OX_ID equal to the OX_ID of the FLOGI.  The D_ID shall be the S_ID",
      "bbox": [
        106.02,
        394.96,
        539.97,
        406.08
      ],
      "block_index": 8,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p154_s0028",
      "text": "of the FLOGI.  This indicates a point-to-point connection with another Nx_Port that is currently",
      "bbox": [
        122.4,
        406.96,
        540.02,
        418.08
      ],
      "block_index": 8,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p154_s0029",
      "text": "busy.  The Nx_Port may proceed to N_Port Login after a delay to allow the destination Nx_Port",
      "bbox": [
        122.4,
        418.96,
        539.87,
        430.08
      ],
      "block_index": 8,
      "line_index": 3,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p154_s0030",
      "text": "to become not busy.",
      "bbox": [
        122.4,
        430.96,
        212.35,
        442.08
      ],
      "block_index": 8,
      "line_index": 4,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p154_s0031",
      "text": "e) F_RJT Sequence with OX_ID equal to the OX_ID of the FLOGI.  The D_ID shall be the S_ID of",
      "bbox": [
        106.02,
        454.96,
        540.02,
        466.08
      ],
      "block_index": 9,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p154_s0032",
      "text": "the FLOGI.  The Fabric has rejected the FLOGI request.  The reason code contained in the",
      "bbox": [
        122.4,
        466.96,
        539.95,
        478.08
      ],
      "block_index": 9,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p154_s0033",
      "text": "Payload determines the Nx_Port’s action.  If the reason code is \"Class not supported\", the",
      "bbox": [
        122.4,
        478.96,
        540.0,
        490.08
      ],
      "block_index": 9,
      "line_index": 3,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p154_s0034",
      "text": "Nx_Port may originate a FLOGI in a different class.  If the reason code is \"Invalid S_ID\", the",
      "bbox": [
        122.4,
        490.96,
        539.95,
        502.07
      ],
      "block_index": 9,
      "line_index": 4,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p154_s0035",
      "text": "Nx_Port may originate a FLOGI with a different S_ID:",
      "bbox": [
        122.4,
        502.96,
        357.9,
        514.07
      ],
      "block_index": 9,
      "line_index": 5,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p154_s0036",
      "text": "A) If the S_ID of the rejected FLOGI was 000000h or 0000h || YY, the Nx_Port may select a 24",
      "bbox": [
        122.4,
        526.96,
        540.05,
        538.07
      ],
      "block_index": 10,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p154_s0037",
      "text": "bit value, XXXXXX, for its N_Port_ID by a method outside this standard and originate a",
      "bbox": [
        138.0,
        538.96,
        539.94,
        550.07
      ],
      "block_index": 10,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p154_s0038",
      "text": "FLOGI with this value in the S_ID.",
      "bbox": [
        138.0,
        550.96,
        288.48,
        562.07
      ],
      "block_index": 10,
      "line_index": 3,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p154_s0039",
      "text": "B) If the S_ID of the rejected FLOGI was XXXXXX, the Nx_Port may select a value of '00 00",
      "bbox": [
        122.4,
        574.96,
        539.99,
        586.07
      ],
      "block_index": 11,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p154_s0040",
      "text": "00' or '00 00 yy', or a new value 'XX XX XX' for its N_Port_ID by a method outside this stan-",
      "bbox": [
        138.0,
        586.96,
        540.06,
        598.07
      ],
      "block_index": 11,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p154_s0041",
      "text": "dard and originate a FLOGI with this value in the S_ID.",
      "bbox": [
        138.0,
        598.96,
        380.18,
        610.07
      ],
      "block_index": 11,
      "line_index": 3,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p154_s0042",
      "text": "f)",
      "bbox": [
        106.02,
        622.96,
        112.13,
        634.07
      ],
      "block_index": 12,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p154_s0043",
      "text": "P_RJT Sequence, with OX_ID equal to the OX_ID of the FLOGI.  The D_ID shall be the S_ID",
      "bbox": [
        122.38,
        622.96,
        539.94,
        634.07
      ],
      "block_index": 12,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p154_s0044",
      "text": "of the FLOGI.  This indicates a point-to-point connection with another Nx_Port.  The reason",
      "bbox": [
        122.4,
        635.02,
        539.96,
        646.13
      ],
      "block_index": 12,
      "line_index": 3,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p154_s0045",
      "text": "code contained in the Payload determines the Nx_Port’s action.  If the reason code is \"Class",
      "bbox": [
        122.4,
        647.02,
        539.95,
        658.13
      ],
      "block_index": 12,
      "line_index": 4,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p154_s0046",
      "text": "not supported\", the Nx_Port may proceed to N_Port Login in a different class than used for the",
      "bbox": [
        122.4,
        659.02,
        540.14,
        670.13
      ],
      "block_index": 12,
      "line_index": 5,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p154_s0047",
      "text": "FLOGI.  For other reason codes, the Nx_Port should respond accordingly.",
      "bbox": [
        122.4,
        671.02,
        449.58,
        682.13
      ],
      "block_index": 12,
      "line_index": 6,
      "span_index": 1
    }
  ],
  "asset_ids": []
}